text:
Park Ave. Tunnel entrance, north from 33rd Street, during the construction of the Subway. The house on the left, occupies the future site of the Vanderbilt Hotel. Directly opposite at the N.W. corner of 34th Street, appears the Community Church of New York.
December 1, 1900.
William B. Parsons Collection.

(1)
Park Avenue at 34th Street, looking northwest from One Park Avenue building at 33rd Street. In the left foreground is shown the north wing of the Vanderbilt Hotel, and in the right foreground
the tower of the Seventy-First Regiment Armory.
Down on the N.w. corner of 34th Street the Community Church (1867) is being demolished to make room for an apartment house.
February 27, 1931.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
(2)
Another view of Park Ave., west side, from East 34th to 35th Streets.
February 22, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
A closer view of the Community Church.
March 21, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS. THE NEW YORK PUBLIC LIBRARY
TILDEN PUBLICATIONS
